# Astro Component Standards

## Component Structure

1. Frontmatter first (imports, Props interface, destructure)
2. HTML template after `---`

```astro
---
import type { HTMLAttributes } from 'astro/types'

interface Props extends HTMLAttributes<'a'> {
	variant?: 'highlight' | 'subtle'
}

const { variant = 'subtle', ...rest } = Astro.props
---

<a {...rest}><slot /></a>
```

## Props

- Define `interface Props` with optional `extends HTMLAttributes<'element'>` for passthrough
- Destructure `Astro.props` in frontmatter
- Use `^_` prefix for intentionally unused props (e.g. `title: _title`)

## Slots

- Use `<slot />` for default content
- Use named slots: `<slot name="seo" />` when layout has multiple insertion points

## Component Naming

- PascalCase for components: `Header`, `Link`, `TagLinks`
- Use kebab-case for file names: `skip-nav-link.astro`, `tag-links.astro`

## Accessibility

- Use `aria-label` for icons without visible text; `aria-hidden="true"` for decorative
- Use `sr-only` for visually hidden content (e.g. screen-reader-only titles)
- Use `SkipNavLink` / `SkipNavContent` for skip links
